  "escalationRequired": false,
  "rootCause": "The previous docs layout mixed owner categories and plan lifecycle state in shallow folders, so both humans and agents had to infer document placement from filenames and status labels. Tooling also encoded old flat paths directly, which would make future document moves brittle and could leave stale path references in lint fixtures, harness prompts, workflow helpers, and recurrence closeout evidence.",
  "prevention": "Use docs/index.md as the tree registry and route new document placement through docs/owners/{operations,ui-workflow,design,architecture,validation} or docs/plans/{current,active,reference,historical}. Docs-lint now classifies progress, active plans, and doc_id prefixes by helpers rather than one-off flat-path checks, while rule-harness/workflow references use the new tree. This change preserves existing hard-fail coverage for index coverage, doc_id path prefix drift, Plan Mode owner routing, active plan artifact owner shape drift, active plan concrete artifact owner collision, progress evidence overload, Fresh Evidence Discipline, and recurrence closeout requirements.",
  "verification": "node --test tools/docs-lint/tests/docs-lint.test.mjs passed with deleted-path closeout coverage; npm run --silent rules:lint passed; rg scoped to AGENTS.md docs tools .codex/skills and this migration shard found no stale flat owner/progress paths; powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\\tools\\check-unity-asset-hygiene.ps1 passed.",
